# UAT Test Case Generator

> **Purpose:** This document specifies how to generate UAT test case Excel files (`.xlsx`) from a PRD, BRD, or feature spec. Use it as a system prompt or instruction block for any AI coding tool (Codex, Cursor, etc.) to produce correctly formatted, tester-ready UAT test case files.

---

## Column Schema (8 columns, always in this order)

| Column | Header | Purpose |
|--------|--------|---------|
| A | # | Sequential test case number. Leave blank on section header rows. |
| B | Priority | `High` or `Medium` — see Priority Rules below |
| C | Case Title & Description | Section label on first row of a new group (e.g. `"9.2 – 1:N Solution ID Logic"`). Blank on subsequent rows of same section. |
| D | PIC | Person or role executing the test. Derive from the roles defined in the PRD. |
| E | Steps | Numbered steps. Use `\n` for line breaks. Include UAT URLs where available. |
| F | Expected results | Bullet points using `*`. One expected result per step where possible. Include exact error messages from spec. **Note:** header uses lowercase "r" — `"Expected results"` not `"Expected Results"` |
| G | Pass/Fail/Skip | Leave blank unless instructed. |
| H | Remarks | Optional: data examples, role clarifications, `"Happy path"`, `"Negative case"` labels. |

---

## Priority Rules

**High** — core functional flows that block the feature from working:
- Upload validation (happy path acceptance)
- Key error/rejection flows (region conflict, serial number errors)
- Multi-role end-to-end flows (vendor submits → assessment → commercial linkage)
- UI field renames that affect navigation or usability
- Assessment access rights and vendor masking

**Medium** — supporting, edge case, or configuration tests:
- Boundary/negative validation cases (0 value, wrong format, gap in sequence)
- Seatalk reminder triggers and message content
- UI label/tooltip details
- Capacity calculation edge cases
- Assign Permission timing restrictions
- Template instruction text checks

---

## Elicitation: Questions to Ask Before Generating

Before generating any test cases, clarify the following if not already clear from context:

1. **Which sections/features to cover?** — Present all BRD sections as multi-select options.
2. **Who are the PICs?** — Derive role names from the PRD. Confirm with the user if any roles are ambiguous.
3. **Pass/Fail/Skip pre-fill preference?** — Options: Pre-fill all as `Pass` / Leave blank / Pre-fill `Pass` + mark unbuilt as `Skip`
4. **Negative/error cases?** — For upload validation or form logic: Both happy path + error / Happy path only / Error only
5. **UAT environment URLs?** — Options: Use `ops.ssc.uat.shopeemobile.com` URLs / Add manually later / Use `[UAT_BASE_URL]` placeholders
6. **Sheet structure** *(always clarify — never assume)*: Does this project have existing Phase 1 test cases on a separate sheet, or should everything go on one sheet? Options: Separate sheets (e.g. `P1` / `P2`) / Single sheet
7. **Preview one section first?** — Always offer to preview the most complex section (upload validation + multi-role flow) before building the full file.

### Optional / Situational

8. **Pass rate tracker?** — If requested, add it to the RIGHT of the header row on each test sheet (columns J–K), NOT on a separate sheet:

   | Col J (Label) | Col K (Formula) |
   |---|---|
   | pass rate | `=COUNTIF(G3:G10000,"Pass")/COUNTIF(A3:A10000,"<>")` formatted as % |
   | Total Cases | `=COUNTIF(A3:A10000,"<>")` |
   | Pass | `=COUNTIF(G3:G10000,"Pass")` |
   | Fail | `=COUNTIF(G3:G10000,"Fail")` |
   | Skip | `=COUNTIF(G3:G10000,"Skip")` |
   | Remaining (blank) | `=COUNTIF(A3:A10000,"<>")-COUNTIF(G3:G10000,"<>")` |

   > Key formula note: Denominator always uses `COUNTIF(A3:A10000,"<>")` (column A, `#` column) — NOT column G. This excludes section header rows (blank `#`) and empty rows. Range is intentionally oversized to pick up new rows dynamically.

9. **问题list (bug tracker) sheet?** — Only include if explicitly requested. Schema: `#`, `Date`, `Question`, `Remark`, `Status`, `Comment`

