## Test Case Writing Rules

### Section Headers
Insert a section header row before each logical group:
- `#` = blank
- `Priority` = `"High"`
- `Case Title` = `"9.2 – Feature Name"` (BRD section number + short label)
- All other columns blank

### Step Writing
- Use numbered steps: `1. Do X\n2. Click Y\n3. Check Z`
- Be specific about navigation paths: `Bid Management → Solution Management → Bid Solution`
- For time-triggered events (Seatalk, emails): instruct tester to manipulate UAT date
- For file uploads: specify what the file contains (e.g. `"数字编号 = 1, 2, 4 (gap at 3)"`)
- Include UAT URLs inline in steps where known (e.g. `https://ops.ssc.uat.shopeemobile.com/...`)

### Expected Results Writing
- Column header is `"Expected results"` (lowercase r)
- Use `*` bullets
- Quote exact error messages from the BRD verbatim
- For UI changes: list every renamed field explicitly
- For calculations: include numeric examples from BRD where provided

### Priority Assignment Per Test Case
Within a section, the happy path acceptance test is usually `High`; negative/edge/format cases are usually `Medium`.

### Negative Test Case Patterns (always include for upload/form features)
For any field with validation, generate test cases for:
- Valid value (happy path) → `High`
- Boundary value (e.g. exactly 0, exactly at limit) → `Medium`
- Out-of-range value (e.g. negative, exceeds max) → `Medium`
- Wrong format (e.g. letters in numeric field, wrong decimal places) → `Medium`
- Missing/blank (if field is mandatory) → `Medium`
- Multi-value comma-separated (if spec mentions comma-separated input) → `Medium`

### Multi-Role Flows
When a feature involves multiple roles (e.g. Procurement creates → Vendor uploads → LH Team assesses), write separate test cases per role action in sequence. Set the `PIC` column accurately per step.

### Seatalk / Automated Reminders
- Test trigger condition (date manipulation in UAT) → `Medium` priority
- Test message title matches spec exactly
- Test message body includes correct placeholders (`[Bid ID]`, `[Expiration Date]`)
- Test send frequency (1x/day, 2x/day, once)

